#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SessionStart hook: inject the SDLC lifecycle gate in project repos.
# Emits nothing outside git repos (global-config sessions, scratch dirs).
#
# source=compact swaps the routing text for compaction recovery: mid-task
# the standard "start the lifecycle" text is a no-op (the summary says
# orientation already happened), while the thing that is actually true —
# the conversation above is now a paraphrase, not evidence — goes unsaid.
# Every other source, and any input we cannot parse, gets the standard
# gate: a wrong recovery injection at real session start would be worse
# than a redundant standard one after compaction.
[ "${AI_SDLC_SCRATCH:-}" = "1" ] && exit 0
git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0

session_source=""
if [ ! -t 0 ] && command -v jq >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  session_source=$(cat 2>/dev/null | jq -r '.source // empty | strings' 2>/dev/null || true)
fi

if [ "$session_source" = "compact" ]; then
  cat <<'COMPACT_EOF'
SDLC COMPACTION RECOVERY (installed policy):
Your context was just compacted: the conversation above is now a summary — a paraphrase, not evidence. Before continuing:
1. Re-read .ai-sdlc/state.md and the in-flight plan; where they contradict the summary, the files win.
2. Do not build on a pre-compaction claim (a passing test, a completed step) without re-establishing it — re-run the command now.
3. If work completed before compaction is not yet recorded in state.md (task statuses, run stamps), checkpoint it there before starting new work.
The lifecycle still applies: Skill(sdlc-start) to re-plan if the goal is no longer clear, Skill(sdlc-finish) before any done/ship claim.
COMPACT_EOF
  exit 0
fi

cat <<'EOF'
SDLC LIFECYCLE (installed policy):
1. Invoke Skill(sdlc-start) before the first substantive task of the session, and again to plan any multi-step or risky change. Small, reversible, obvious edits may go straight to the change.
2. Execution is governed by the engineering standard (sdlc-core/references/STANDARD.md): root cause over patch, smallest coherent change, verification ladder.
3. Invoke Skill(sdlc-finish) before claiming any change is done, verified, or ready to ship — however small the edit — and before the session ends if anything changed; it is what makes the project resumable by the next session.
Scale ceremony with blast radius, not file count. The carve-out in (1) exempts the edit, never the claim: a done/ship verdict is high blast radius by itself — the next session builds on it unchecked — and so is config that propagates to other agents/machines, even when the diff is small.
Plugin installs namespace the skills: ai-sdlc:sdlc-start, ai-sdlc:sdlc-finish.
EOF
